cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.SE, cs.CE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the implementation details of a template-based generic programming approach for simulation and analysis of partial differential equations.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper deals with computing additional quantities, such as derivatives, needed for embedded analysis algorithms.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses managing software complexity in multiphysics simulation.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is relevant as the paper deals with simulation and analysis of partial differential equations in a physical application.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses automation of embedded analysis capabilities.
